# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# BROWSER REQUIREMENTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# Chrome  >= 90
# Firefox >= 88
# Edge    >= 90
# Safari  >= 14
#
# Required browser APIs used in this project:
#   - ES6+ (const, let, arrow functions, template literals,
#           destructuring, spread, optional chaining, nullish coalescing)
#   - Fetch API (not used — all data is local)
#   - SVG DOM manipulation
#   - CSS Custom Properties (variables)
#   - localStorage (theme persistence)
#   - requestAnimationFrame
#   - window.print() (PDF export)
#   - Blob + URL.createObjectURL (fallback text download)


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# DATA FILES (included in repo)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────

# data.js
#   - 200 account objects (generated from customer_profiles.csv + account_status.csv)
#   - 1930 transaction objects (generated from transactions.csv)
#   - Exposes: realAccounts[], realTransactions[], accountMap{}, riskSummary{}
#   - Size: ~720 KB

# Source CSVs (NOT included in repo — used only to generate data.js):
#   transactions.csv        — 1930 rows, fields: txn_id, sender, receiver, amount, timestamp, channel, branch
#   customer_profiles.csv   — 200 rows, fields: account, age, profession, income, risk_level
#   account_status.csv      — 200 rows, fields: account, open_date, last_txn, dormant
#   graph_edges.csv         — edge list with branch/amount/channel/timestamp
#   fund_flow.gexf          — graph format (Gephi compatible)
#   fund_flow.graphml       — graph format (Cytoscape compatible)


